10 years 🤍 
How has it gone so fast??
I remember thinking that I never wanted the honeymoon days to end. I didn’t want to get older and let the flame die. 
Let’s be honest.  There is no way to keep those honeymoon days forever. Life changes.  It evolves and grows.  Responsibilities multiply and you start to experience real life together. You hurt each other and you help each other and you support each other and you learn that neither one of you is perfect, and through all of that the honeymoon phase ends and you can begin the phase that in my opinion is much more beautiful. It’s complex and safe and so so incredible.  It’s what I like to think fairytales mean when they say “true love”. 

The day we got married I swore I couldn’t love him more than I did.  What a lie.  My love for him is so exponentially more than it was.  I have never and will never love anyone the way I love him. 
We have done so much together. We made this family together. I truly believe there is nothing we can’t do together and nothing we wouldn’t do for each other.  I want to say that I couldn’t love him more than I do now, but history has taught me that’s not true.  Here is to growing this love more than my brain can comprehend.  I love you Tyler. Happy anniversary ❤️
Holy moly

I think marrying into a family and meshing so easily is a very rare thing.  I feel like I’ve known them my entire life and I feel totally and completely loved and accepted by each one of them. 
This week has shown me just how much love there is in this family. They love each other with everything they have.  They will do anything for each other. 
Somehow I got lucky enough to be invited in and it’s one of my greatest blessings. 

This week has been hard.  But watching everyone surround Kenzie and Tyler has been spiritual for me.  Kenzie naturally is the caretaker.  She is always trying to help and make sure everyone is ok and to see everyone rush to her in pure love is so special. 

I’m rambling but I just feel so overwhelmed with love for them this morning and a public declaration of that love feels appropriate today. 

I love you Porters.  I’m proud of your resilience. I’m proud of the way you support each other. I’m proud to be a part of this family.
We took more photos together at taylor swift than we have our entire 25 year friendship combined.  What a night.

All I know is I love you 💕
